ATTENTION: preliminary state of board support for Raspberry Pi 5
----------------------------------------------------------------

This README file contains information on the contents of the meta-mender-qemu-community layer.

Please see the corresponding sections below for details.

Dependencies
============

  URI: https://git.yoctoproject.org/poky
  branch: kirkstone

  URI: https://git.openembedded.org/meta-openembedded
  branch: kirkstone

  URI: https://github.com/swiftbot-labs/meta-mender
  branch: kirkstone

  URI: https://github.com/agherzan/meta-raspberrypi
  branch: kirkstone

Contributions
=============

Please the README file in the top level directory.


I. Adding the meta-mender-raspberrypi-community layer to your build
=================================================

Run 'bitbake-layers add-layer meta-mender-raspberrypi-community'

II. Misc
========

The layer supports building for Raspberry Pi 5. Add the following to your configuration:

UBOOT_MACHINE = "rpi_arm64_config"
COMPATIBLE_MACHINE:pn-u-boot:raspberrypi5:forcevariable = "(raspberrypi5)"
PREFERRED_VERSION_u-boot = "2024.04"
PREFERRED_VERSION_u-boot-tools = "2024.04"